UBA's Kenyan Unit Posts Narrower Annual Loss as Income From Loans Climbs

-- B y   P a u l   R i c h a r d s o n
-- 
2011-03-31T04:46:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-31/uba-s-kenyan-unit-posts-narrower-annual-loss-as-income-from-loans-climbs.html
United Bank  for Africa Ltd.’s
Kenyan unit posted a smaller full-year loss as income from loans
increased.  The loss totaled 106.6 million shillings ($1.28 million) in
the 12 months through December, compared with 155.4 million
shillings a year earlier, UBA Kenya Bank Ltd. said in a
statement published in the Nairobi-based Daily Nation newspaper
today. Net interest income, the money banks earn from interest
charges on loans, grew 68 percent to 66.6 million shillings, it
said.  United Bank is Nigeria’s fourth-biggest lender by market
value.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  